column5: Just came back from my grandparents, and I was fortunate to see some animal activity!  My dad at first spotted a doe, and with some patience, I watched another 3 more does emerge from the bush. While watcigng them feed, I noticed somediturbance just past them, luckly enough, a coyote came out of the bush to check out the deer!  Though, the yote' didn't seem very interested in the deer, so it eventually ran off. I attempted some shots at the deer, but they were too far off to get a clear view, but I was able to get some pictures, quality wasnt very satisfying, but I didn't have my zoom-in lens
Cool pictures, i think i can see them out there lol.  Thanks for sharing!  Ask how to use photobucket then u can make ur pictures nice and big, not reduced
There tough to see, but hey, its the best I could do without a zoom-in lens!  But I shall try and get some better pics eventually!
Memo to Santa for next year.............   Please bring Profisher25 new digital camera with zoom lense
I actually plan on buying a new zoom-in lens for my digital camera,, but for these pictures, i used my DSLR.
There's TWO bunnies in the third pic.
